column29:
In RuntimeDataServiceImpl (https://github.com/kiegroup/jbpm/pull/871/files or JBPM-6068) following static initialization was added:
{code}
private UserGroupCallback userGroupCallback = UserDataServiceProvider.getUserGroupCallback();
{code}

This leads to default-initialization of MvelUserGroupCallbackImpl, which is supposed to be used only in test-context (see Comment #1 in https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1316974#c1).

Further implications is the run of automatic service-discovery by scanning provided kie.conf-files of jbpm-libraries (see Steps to Reproduce).

column160:
25/Sep/18 7:41 AM;swiderski.maciej;that's correct that default is Mvel based one but you can easily change it via system properties:
{code}
-Dorg.jbpm.ht.callback=ldap
{code}
this was done on purpose so you don't have to modify the binary package such as kie-server.war file. See java docs of UserDataServiceProvider for all details what you can set
